snippet.textDisplay:
You know, most (if not all) of the countries with the highest average intelligence have significantly more emphasis on testing over school and homework...

However, IQ tests are largely bogus. While there is certainly a correlation of logic and intelligence, it is by no means consistent enough to make any sort of definite system to gauge it. I have incredibly smart and/or creative friends and acquaintances who've scored lower on official IQ tests than some of my duller ones, and vice-versa. You can be as dumb as dirt but have exceptional reasoning abilities, or be able to easily comprehend even the most complicated subjects while lacking those, and by the logic of these tests, you would be deemed stupid.


The point is, grading intelligence based almost purely on logical ability over the whole spectrum is simply a poor way to conduct these tests, but the human mind is so complex that it's nearly impossible to make a comprehensive test that covers every necessary base.
